Wouldn&#39;t it make more sense to have an S3ClientFactory which has a static method *createSessionWithAssumeRoleCredentials* which creates an S3 client for the set of credential that you pass? Credentials are required to instantiate an S3 client, so have a createSessionWithAssumeRoleCredentials method on an S3Client instance makes little sense.

